    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Romero</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 27, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                                the enclosed<note n="*" xml:id="d383fn1">For enclosure see
                                    correspondence with United States minister to Mexico, May 27,
                                    1867.</note> telegram has been received this morning from Mr.
                                Plumb, at New Orleans.</p>
                <p>I avail myself of this opportunity to renew the assurance of my high
                                consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Señor Don <hi rend="smallcaps">Matias Romero,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c. &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
